TextBlock.TextLine: Antw 8 August
Lille Richd Southell
Sr. in answer to yd of 6t. curitt my thanckes for yd letter to T.S. I hope
I shall gett cleare of him, I heare nothing of his preformed
if I could do him service I would do itt: our trade here is o toghether
ast ostand and hath been ever sence may & butt little hopes for florishing
because wee have a raport as if the french were entred the payes dewaer
this day, pretending Helft & severall villages to the gates of Gant: I have
all my winter provision a coming from bruges & may be now ready to
come from theme, & upon this news I am much alarmed not
knowing what to do, for feare that the french should sease upon
them between gant & this please so could wish I had yd advise
for I am unload the goods att gane
@9 Augusti 1681
Leuven Joande Goede
Mons. Aot antwoort aenden ul van 6 deser sende hier ingesloten estalen van
coleur de spine lakens waer van N.662 het naeste aen ul stael comt maer
10 in de 50 ellen lanck te van ƒ4:4:-soo dat sonder ul perticuliere ordre niet
endirue senden staen eenigh van dese ul aen, laet het mij cato weten en salsen
ul toesenden, ick hebbe un oock schoone fijne lakens van mijn Eyge sabryu
van alle coleuren, waghte ul antwoort alsoo dese coleuren haest
verkoght worden de perpetuanen sullen oock de naefte weeke gedaen sijn
kan ul mij eenigh gelt sende sal opt kooghste willecom sjn
en sal ul oock wel doen mits ick ben
gent francois Herrebout N:660: a ƒ4
mons. verwachte heden oft moogen tot gent te arriveeren een pertije packen
doch soo bekomen wij tijdinge van Rijssel dat de fransen in mars sijn naert
lant van Helft, ende be liggende dorpen onder sent soo ben seer beducht
ofte sij onse goederen die naer dermonde soude passeren, souden aenstaen
ende vermeesteren, oversulx soo eenigh waertheyt is dat de franse intlant
van telft sonder sijn, soo vinde geraden het schip costij ofte houden, ende
de goeederen tot dat wij meerder securiteiyt daer van hebben, want liver
mijn goederen coste wille doen lossen, als waer te loopen soo verwacht
ul advies tegens morgen avont sonder faut blijvee
@ 9 ditto 1681
Brugge Rap: Coots
mijnrt sedert mijnen van 6 deser den ul van 4 ditto bekomen thomas barber
was gearriveert t selve hope heden van klerck te verstaen er ende dat
de goeder soo wel als die van Hullat terwarts sullen sonversonden
ingesloten de versoeghte certificatie. wij bekomen soo tijd ing van bijsel
al ofte de fransen in mars waren naert lant van helft onge op discretie
te leven, d' welke waersijnde anonse goederen van gent herrewaerts wel
ongemaeck mogt causeeren doch verhope niee waer mede blijve
C 9 aug 1681
Londen mr. Edmund Warner
mij last to you was on the 30th pase, sence non from you, yett hope thatt you have well
receaved the 2 packetts from Italy. Inclosed send you the acctt of charges on them, as also
of the cost & charges of one packett of our, countrey laces, which are sent to newporte
easterday, to come over with these letters, I wish itt safe in ye postession, & thatt itt may
prove to content incoridgement for more, I amsure t is as well assorted, & bought as itt
can be practised, I here fore hope it will render, boath proffitt & content, as for the prou
is ordinary 5 yett to give you wath advantidges, I can in that trade have charged
with 4 onely, my disbours ad. In all is £135.5 ƒ vlemish accordingh to the inclosed
note for wich have valued on you £76.1101 att 35.4 att 2120 in favour of mr. Jac
Bouwens, for the valeu of the same, which pleases to give, dec. honour, & note accordingly
In Antwerp, 9 August
London Abram vivian
th
Sr. my last to you was on the 6: curitt: sence recd. both yd of 22 & 25: past I amsorrs
pindar brings no baile of fine cloth & now them I want most as last yeare
I did the dozins, yett hope that smith will bring the rest of the in ordered
goods & where as you supose he will tarry to long, so itt will be as well to
dispatch 2 bale of fine northrens by the vere first for Rotterdam to my
order, n'ay rather then faile butt one bale the bale N. 41: promises vere well
by the pattarnes & as yett am of opinion that m. potter shall be the man
butt when all the goods are here shall be able enought to iudge the need full
I wont have mr. Potter to pick the best goods to make up the last bale of fine
northrens thought he should pay al togheter about 5 18 ayd raw, be cause I want
some of the vere best northrens, so pray write him this, if itt be not to late
& that yd order be complented: I have accepted yd bill for my acctt. according
to order: wee do not know how things will go on this side, because the french
demand almost all our countrey I could wish: wee were att rest to drive our trade
with case whist I exspected to understand from you what passes further
in our concens the goods out of pindar are on their way from Bruges hether
London Henry Maynard
@ 9 ditto -
th
Sr. my last to you was on the 6: curitt when remitted you £150:-:- att 354½ on mr.
will scawens for yd acctt & £128:6:7 on me bounell for my acctt. which
I hope is will comes to yd handes, now have before mee yd of 25 past when you
come, you will be welcom & I hope finde all things to content, intrim barbar
is well arrived, as much I exspected to have of Ben: Clarck you wonder
that I give no orders for northren goods, I have enought for these 3 monthes, so shall
in order non till I see you for though m. Hill doth indifferent well, yett finde
not those advantages as by others I have & which I'll shew you when here in
the meane while wee much feare the french disturbance, for I doubt
they will take all our countrey, before any naigbours shall be awake
& wee our selfs are not att all in a expacttie to defend itt inclosed acctt. of
sale of Julij last, which I hope you shall finde right, mony is extreame
sale of july scarey, yett shall do on my side all what you can exspect from
@ 10 ditto 1681
Gent francois Herrebout
monsr. gisteren was aen ul mijnen laesten sedert verstaen van brugge dat 13 packen
voor mij ul waren toegesonden de welke hope oock wel sijn geworden, ende middts
het seijnt seker te wesen, dat de franscheliggen bj pond si pierre ontreayt
deviviere soo twijffele oft eenige schepen sullen mogen passeren, voordatte
sij hinne pretentie voldaen sijn, en al hoe wel andere kinne goeduren
lieten depescheren, soo wil ick mijnen intrest gedwerteert hebbe deade het niet
versonden voor dat het ander gepasseirt is, soo dan is saecke dat een schip pertreck
herrewoeerts laet daer in laden alleenlijk MN 26: 30 & 31 met Rt44:
en 46 sijn 5 packen de 2 packen MN 29 & 32: sal ul apart houden want die
p wagen wel moght on biden, dander ses tot naeder ordre te bewaeren
soo gelieft daer goede sorge voor te dragen, ondat ick aen geongeluck en gerake, ver
wacht heden ul advies vant geene gepasseirt is en volgens dien sal morgen
brader scrijven midts Blijve
daer moeten in alles 4 packen onvrij verklaert wordens a gouverno
@ 1 ditto 168
Brugge Raphael Coots
volgens den ul van 8 & 11 deser syn hiet lof de besende packen mij gewoorden. het stoght gonen gelt
frisaert woorts & aldereersten gesonden, daer over de satisfactie van den ontfanger van sijn maytr
reghten verwaghte, mits dat ciiel sal belasten renvoyeere de staelen alsoo die niet noodigh hebbe
oocq voor 42 st mij niet sonden aenstaen, de reeg van oncosten sal examineeren & verlanghe
naer het arrivem. van Beniamin elerct, 't welck morgen hope te verstaen, wesens ul verkoghte
dosijnen, sal ten eersten de reeq. seijnden, alsoo veele beletselen tot nogh 't selve hebben verhindert
1 gepasseerde, verneme geerne
